column13: Adana Demirspor has a terrible defense, conceding 34 goals in 14 games so far, averaging 2.43 per game.Furthermore, they have conceded three or more goals in three of their last four games.Besiktas is also not solid defensively and has kept a clean sheet only once in their last five games.In the last three direct meetings between the teams, three or more goals have been scored in two of the matches.This makes the likelihood of a high-scoring match very high.

Both teams are expected to score in the match between Galatasaray and Trabzonspor due to the weak defense of both teams.Galatasaray, despite its strong offense and no loss so far in the season, has not been solid on defense, conceding only one goal in the last nine games.Trabzonspor has also had problems defensively, having recorded just two clean sheets in the last nine games and in seven of those both teams scored.So, in view of these trends, both teams are likely to score.

We expect both teams to score in the match between Lazio and Inter due to Lazio's strong offense and Inter's tendency to concede at least one goal against them.Lazio regularly score at least one goal at home, having done so in 22 of their last 23 home games.On the other hand, Inter, despite their solid defense, has conceded a goal against this opponent in 4 of the last 5 meetings between the two teams.

Bournemouth look very strong in the current season, having won their last three games and are in good form, with 24 points in 15 rounds.They are very strong at home, winning 4 of their last 5 games on home turf.On the other hand, West Ham have problems away, having lost three of their last four away games.Also, the quality between the two teams is quite different and favours Bournemouth.

The first match ended in a 2-2 draw, but in this rematch both teams will approach with more caution, avoiding risks in attack.Silkeborg have had games with few goals lately, with only one of their last six games having more than two goals.Aalborg also have problems in attack, having not scored in their last two league games.These factors, along with the importance of advancing to the next round, make it unlikely that we will see goals in this match.

column3: Half Time / Full Time - Braga / Braga
column13: Braga have a solid record at home with seven wins from their last 11 games at the Estádio Municipal de Braga despite some problems in defence.They have scored in most of their home games, while Famalicao has had consistency problems on the road, going winless in their last four games.The quality of the home side is much better and we expect them to win convincingly.

column3: Half Time / Full Time - Porto / Porto
column13: Porto are in magnificent form at home, winning all seven of their league games, five of them by at least two goals.On the other hand, Estrela are winless in their last 19 away games in the Premeira Liga and have serious problems in attack, having scored just one goal in their last five away games.We expect Porto to beat their opponent very easily today.
